Long Island Rail Road to Run Reduced Rush-Hour Schedule as Tracks Repaired

-- B y   S t e v e n   F r o m m
-- 
2011-05-10T17:50:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-10/long-island-rail-road-to-run-reduced-rush-hour-schedule-as-tracks-repaired.html
The Long Island Rail Road said it
will operate a “significantly reduced” afternoon rush schedule
of trains from  Penn Station .  Of the 87 trains normally operated out of Penn Station
during the afternoon rush, 20 will be canceled and combined with
other trains. The information was disclosed in an e-mailed
statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steven Fromm at 
 sfromm@bloomberg.net  